[{"id":"VR187042","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of f in the x y coordinate plane, with the origin labeled O. The numbers negative 2 through 3, in increments of 1, are indicated on the x axis. The numbers negative 1 and 1 are indicated on the y axis. The graph consists of two line segments. The first line segment begins at the point with coordinates negative 2 comma negative 1, and moves upward and to the right. It crosses the x axis at negative 1 and ends on the y axis at 1. The second line segment begins where the first ends, and moves downward and to the right. It crosses the x axis at 2 and ends at the point with coordinates 3 comma negative 0.5.\" height=\"186\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR187042.g05.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The graph of the function <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\"><math alttext=\"f\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> consists of two line segments, as shown in the figure above. Let <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> be the function&nbsp;defined by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g of x equals, the integral from negative 2 to x, of, f of t, d t\"><math alttext=\"g of x equals, the integral from negative 2 to x, of, f of t, d t\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mrow><msubsup><mrow><mo>∫</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></msubsup><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>ⅆ</mo><mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mrow></mstyle></mrow></math></span></span>. At what value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> does <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"g\"><math alttext=\"g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> attain its global maximum on the closed interval <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open bracket, negative 2 comma 3, close bracket\"><math alttext=\"open bracket, negative 2 comma 3, close bracket\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR187042_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 2\"><math alttext=\"negative 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 1\"><math alttext=\"negative 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0\"><math alttext=\"0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]